article.description:
Takia Starks led Texas A&M (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today) with 18 
points as the Aggies beat Missouri 62-43 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Starks scores 18 as Texas A&M handles Missouri
article.linkText: Starks helps No. 23 Texas A&M run over Missouri
article.story:
COLLEGE STATION, Texas (AP) -- Takia Starks led Texas A&M (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today) with 18
points as the Aggies beat Missouri 62-43 on Tuesday night.

	   Starks hit three jumpers in the first four minutes as the Aggies
jumped out to an 8-0 lead.

	   Missouri turned the ball over 19 times in the first half as
Texas A&M (15-6, 3-4 Big 12) coasted to a 36-23 halftime lead. The
Aggies never trailed in the game.

	   Missouri cut the lead to nine with 11 minutes to play but the
Aggies went on a 13-2 run over the next five minutes to stretch
their lead to 20 with six minutes remaining.

	   Danielle Gant added 16 points for Texas A&M and Patrice Reado
had 11. La Toya Micheaux led the team with 10 rebounds.

	   Shakara Jones led Missouri (8-12, 1-6) with 15 points on 7-of-8
field goal shooting. Alyssa Hollins added 12 points.

	   The Aggies shot 36 percent from the field to the Tigers' 43
percent. Texas A&M won the rebounding contest, 40-33.
